4
00:02:06,971 --> 00:02:10,257
Into my heart an air that kills

5
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:13,636
From yon far country blows

6
00:02:13,811 --> 00:02:16,563
What are those blue remembered hills

7
00:02:16,731 --> 00:02:21,227
What spires, what farms are those?

8
00:02:21,402 --> 00:02:24,107
That is the land of lost content

9
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:27,198
I see it shining plain

10
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:31,115
The happy highways where I went

11
00:02:31,287 --> 00:02:34,822
And cannot come again

12
00:02:37,001 --> 00:02:41,248
(♪ Piano continues to murmur...)

13
00:03:10,076 --> 00:03:13,943
I met a traveller from an antique land
who said:

14
00:03:14,122 --> 00:03:19,033
Two vast and trunk less legs of stone
stand in the desert

15
00:03:19,210 --> 00:03:22,875
And on the pedestal
these words appear:

16
00:03:23,047 --> 00:03:26,167
"My name is Ozymandias,
King of Kings:

17
00:03:26,342 --> 00:03:30,589
"Look on my works, ye mighty,
and despair!."

18
00:03:30,763 --> 00:03:33,515
Nothing beside remains

19
00:03:33,683 --> 00:03:38,345
Round the decay of
that colossal wreck, boundless and bare

20
00:03:38,521 --> 00:03:44,690
The lone and level sands
stretch far away

21
