Music for the Royal Fireworks )

23
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:03,331
(♪ Trumpet voluntary
accompanied by brisk drumming)

24
00:04:45,713 --> 00:04:49,663
(♪ Trumpet ornamentation continues...)

25
00:05:02,438 --> 00:05:07,349
(♪ Trumpet music concludes
with a flourish)

26
00:05:09,821 --> 00:05:14,447
We love the place we hate,
then hate the place we love

27
00:05:14,617 --> 00:05:16,526
We leave the place we love,

28
00:05:16,702 --> 00:05:20,617
then spend a lifetime trying to regain it.

29
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,742
Come closer now...

30
00:05:24,919 --> 00:05:28,122
...and see your dreams.

31
00:05:28,297 --> 00:05:33,458
Come closer now... and see mine.

32
00:05:37,014 --> 00:05:40,051
No meat on Friday.
Confession on Saturday,

33
00:05:40,226 --> 00:05:44,306
emerging cleansed
and pleasing to God.

34
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:48,264
Mass on Sundays,
and Holy days of obligation.

35
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:53,321
Despite my dogged piety,
no great revelation came.

36
00:05:53,489 --> 00:05:56,905
No divine balm to ease my soul.

37
00:05:57,076 --> 00:05:59,911
Just years wasted in useless prayer.

38
00:06:01,747 --> 00:06:06,244
If I pray long enough,
I would be forgiven.

39
00:06:06,419 --> 00:06:10,333
If I am forgiven,
I would be made whole.

40
00:06:10,506 --> 00:06:14,420
All I'll need then is the girl.

41
00:06:15,678 --> 00:06:19,261
Suddenly, I knew, suddenly, I thought...

42
00:06:19,432 --> 00:06:22,219
...it's all a lie.

43
00:06:22,393 --> 00:06:24,516
Paradise betrayed.

44
00:06:24,687 --> 00:06:27,225
There was no God, only Satan,

45
00:06:27,398 --> 00:06:33,234
sauntering behind me with a smirk,
saying, "I'll get you in the end".

46
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:38,824
Tu es Petrus.
You're a brick, Pete.

47
00:06:41,078 --> 00:06:43,865
Here, people married.

48
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,661
Here, people died and were buried.

49
00:06:46,834 --> 00:06:48,992
In deconsecrated Catholic Churches,

50
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:53,582
