109
00:11:45,841 --> 00:11:51,001
(♪ Johnnie "Scat" Davis:
Hooray For Hollywood)

110
00:11:54,850 --> 00:11:58,053
At seven, I saw Gene Kelly
and Singin'in the Rain

111
00:11:58,229 --> 00:12:03,982
and discovered the movies, loved them
and swallowed them whole.

112
00:12:08,155 --> 00:12:10,776
And my love was as muscular
as my Catholicism,

113
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:15,576
but without any of the drawbacks.
Musicals, Melodramas, Westerns,

114
00:12:15,746 --> 00:12:19,447
nothing was too rich or too poor
for my rapacious appetite

115
00:12:19,625 --> 00:12:24,832
and I gorged myself with a frequency
that would shame a sinner.

116
00:12:28,759 --> 00:12:31,428
But soon, darker pleasures.

117
00:12:31,595 --> 00:12:34,881
At 15, I saw Dirk Bogarde
in Victim

118
00:12:35,057 --> 00:12:38,841
and discovered something
entirely different.

119
00:12:41,605 --> 00:12:44,392
And when I was not at the movies,
on Friday nights,

120
00:12:44,566 --> 00:12:48,398
I was at the Liverpool Stadium
watching the wrestling.

121
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:52,438
Not for its pantomimic villainy
but for something more illicit.

122
00:12:52,616 --> 00:12:55,321
And in short, I was afraid.

123
00:12:55,494 --> 00:12:57,819
As I struggled with
my adolescent desires,

124
00:12:57,997 --> 00:12:59,906
as I waited at the top of the aisle,

125
00:13:00,082 --> 00:13:02,490
as the wrestlers swaggered up
from the ring,

126
00:13:02,668 --> 00:13:04,910
their trunks tight across the buttocks,

127
00:13:05,087 --> 00:13:09,215
I could feel their body heat
as I furtively touched a back or a thigh,

128
00:13:09,383 --> 00:13:11,126
choking with schoolboy guilt

129
00:13:11,302 --> 00:13:15,085
and trembling with the fear
of the wrath of God.

130
00:13:15,264 --> 00:13:20,685
Oh, save me from those dark desires
which thrill and compel.

131
00:13:20,853 --> 00:13:25,598
The world. The flesh.
And the Devil.

132
00:13:25,774 --> 00:13:28,728
(Bell rings)

133
00:13:28,902 --> 00:13:34,063
(♪ Male voice sings Perotin's
Beata Viscera )

134
00:13:36,452 --> 00:13:39,322
Caught between Canon
and the criminal law,

135
00:13:39,496 --> 00:13:42,414
I said goodbye to my girlhood.

136
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:54,919
Here, I wept...

137
00:13:55,095 --> 00:13:59,591
...wept and prayed until my knees bled,
but no succour came -

138
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:02,554
no peace granted.

139
00:14:10,903 --> 00:14:13,572
Here was my whole world.

140
00:14:13,739 --> 00:14:18,733
Home. School. The Movies.

141
00:14:18,911 --> 00:14:21,402
And God.

142
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:24,367
You, who damn but give no comfort.

143
00:14:24,541 --> 00:14:26,997
Why do I plead?

144
00:14:27,169 --> 00:14:31,249
Why do you not respond, angel eyes?

145
00:14:33,008 --> 00:14:35,843
Jesus, mercy. Mary, help.

146
00:14:37,262 --> 00:14:39,469
Lull me to safety.

147
00:14:41,266 --> 00:14:44,516
(♪ Plainsong continues...)

148
00:14:49,274 --> 00:14:53,652
Between sleeping and waking,
Earth does not revolve.

149
00:14:53,821 --> 00:14:56,821
And slow turns the life
of meagre timbre,

150
00:14:56,990 --> 00:14:58,900
of dullest breath.

151
00:15:01,578 --> 00:15:04,947
Between birth and dying,
some lovely moments grow.

152
00:15:05,124 --> 00:15:08,078
And sorrows not known until tomorrow,

153
00:15:08,252 --> 00:15:12,499
